WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:11.160
Oxford Bookworms, Stage 1. The Witches of Pendle, Chapter 1, The Peddler

00:11.160 --> 00:21.820
The spring of 1634 arrives. But in the prison of Lancaster Castle, it stays cold. The twenty

00:21.820 --> 00:30.380
women in the prison are dirty, hungry, and cold. There are no beds or chairs, and so

00:30.380 --> 00:39.060
they sleep on the cold floor. There are no windows, so it is always dark.

00:39.060 --> 00:47.380
The women want to get out of the prison. They want to go home. Sometimes the guards open

00:47.380 --> 00:55.300
the big, old door, and put some bread and water on the floor. Then they close the door

00:55.300 --> 01:02.380
again. My name is Janet Device, and I am one of

01:02.380 --> 01:12.940
the twenty women in prison. Day after day, I sit on the cold floor and wait.

01:12.940 --> 01:22.580
I want to feel warm again. I want to see the sky again. And Pendle Hill, the beautiful

01:22.580 --> 01:31.820
hill near my home. But I am in the dark prison of Lancaster Castle, and I sit on the cold

01:31.820 --> 01:43.260
floor and wait. One day, something happens. The guards open the big, old door.

01:43.260 --> 01:54.100
Janet Device, the guard calls. Come here at once, witch. Somebody wants to see you.

01:54.100 --> 02:03.860
I get up, slowly, because I am very cold, and I walk across the dark room to the door.

02:03.860 --> 02:10.100
Perhaps it is someone from Reed Hall. Perhaps I am going home.

02:10.100 --> 02:21.220
Janet Device, be quick. The guard calls again. Someone is standing at the door with the guard.

02:21.220 --> 02:34.820
Janet, he says quietly, I see him then, a tall man with brown hair and tired blue eyes.

02:34.820 --> 02:48.100
He is not from Reed Hall. It is Mr. Webster from the church at Kildwick. My legs stop moving,

02:48.100 --> 03:00.660
and suddenly I want to sit down. Come on, come on! The guard says angrily. He begins to close the door.

03:00.660 --> 03:13.700
Come out here for a minute, Janet. Mr. Webster says quietly, sit down and eat something. I sit down

03:14.180 --> 03:25.060
at a little table near the door. Mr. Webster gives me some bread and some meat, and I begin to eat

03:25.140 --> 03:25.780
hungrily.

03:28.260 --> 03:34.580
Ten minutes, the guard says. After ten minutes, she goes in again.

03:36.740 --> 03:39.300
Thank you, Mr. Webster says.

03:41.940 --> 03:53.620
How is everyone at Reed Hall? I ask at last. Mr. Webster smiles. Everyone is well. I was there

03:53.620 --> 04:05.940
yesterday. I close my eyes for a minute. Mr. Webster, it's not true. I'm not a witch, you know.

04:08.580 --> 04:17.460
I know, Janet, Mr. Webster says, last week I brought Edmund Robinson and his father into my church

04:18.180 --> 04:24.260
and asked them about the boy's story. Many people believed Edmund's story,

04:25.060 --> 04:31.540
but some people didn't. Edmund Robinson is going to London tomorrow with his father,

04:32.660 --> 04:34.740
and a judge is going to question them.

04:37.540 --> 04:41.140
The guard comes back and begins to open the door.

04:42.020 --> 04:53.700
Time, he says. Mr. Webster stands up. God is here with you, Janet. Never forget that.

04:54.900 --> 04:56.980
You can be happy when God is with you.

04:59.460 --> 05:09.860
I stand up too and take the bread from the table. Yes, Mr. Webster. God is with me. I believe that

05:11.460 --> 05:15.140
happy. How can I be happy?

05:18.260 --> 05:23.780
I go back into the dark prison and the guard closes the door behind me.

05:25.300 --> 05:30.660
The women run to me. Bread, give us bread. They cry.

05:32.340 --> 05:37.940
Quickly, I put the bread in my shirt. I don't want to lose it.

05:38.820 --> 05:44.740
I walk across the room and sit down, on the floor.

05:46.260 --> 05:51.220
I am crying, but I feel a little better.

05:52.740 --> 05:57.140
Edmund Robinson of New Church is only ten years old.

05:58.340 --> 06:02.580
Edmund told lies about me and about many women.

06:03.300 --> 06:08.660
He saw us at a witch's meeting, at a house called Horstones.

06:09.860 --> 06:14.020
It's not true, but many people believed him.

06:15.460 --> 06:22.180
What is he going to say in London? The truth or more lies?

06:25.380 --> 06:28.740
But now, in the prison of Lancaster Castle,

06:28.740 --> 06:33.860
in the prison of Lancaster Castle, I want to tell my story.

06:36.340 --> 06:45.460
It is a story about rich men and angry villages, about old women and hungry children.

06:47.540 --> 06:51.620
It is a true story, and it happened to me.

06:51.620 --> 07:02.420
I was born in 1603. My family was always very poor.

07:03.620 --> 07:07.060
And after my father died, we were poorer.

07:09.380 --> 07:14.660
In winter, I was often ill, and I was always cold and hungry.

07:15.060 --> 07:21.460
In summer, I was sometimes ill, and I was often cold and hungry.

07:23.460 --> 07:30.660
We lived some miles from the village of New Church, in an old house called Mulkin Tower.

07:31.860 --> 07:34.660
It was dirty and cold.

07:36.660 --> 07:40.660
The rain came in through the windows, and there were no doors.

07:40.660 --> 07:48.340
To the west was the big hill called Pendle.

07:50.500 --> 07:52.580
Pendle Hill was beautiful.

07:54.980 --> 08:01.300
I loved Pendle Hill because it sat quietly all year and watched me.

08:01.300 --> 08:10.340
My story begins on the 18th day of March, in the year 1612.

08:13.140 --> 08:18.660
I was nine years old, and my life began to change on that day.

08:21.460 --> 08:28.260
My mother and my grandmother were ill, and they sat on the floor with their dogs,

08:29.140 --> 08:30.340
near the little fire.

08:33.460 --> 08:36.180
My sister, Alison, wanted to go out.

08:38.660 --> 08:41.460
I'm going to look for bread, she said.

08:43.620 --> 08:47.940
My brother, James, sat near the fire. His mouth opened.

08:49.860 --> 08:53.140
Go and look for bread, he said. Go and look for bread.

08:54.020 --> 08:57.780
James often said things again and again.

09:00.580 --> 09:05.300
Alison ran out of the house, and I followed her.

09:07.300 --> 09:10.420
Go and look for bread, James called.

09:12.580 --> 09:19.620
Alison began to go east, up the hill, and path the big trees behind Mulkin Tower.

09:19.940 --> 09:32.180
Alison walked fast, she was 18 years old, and she was tall, with long, dirty brown hair,

09:33.060 --> 09:35.380
and a white, hungry face.

09:37.700 --> 09:40.820
It was cold, but there was no rain.

09:41.540 --> 09:50.180
Alison wore a coat, and some shoes, but I had no coat, and no shoes.

09:51.700 --> 09:59.220
Please, wait a minute, I call to my sister, I want to come with you.

10:00.900 --> 10:06.340
No, Alison cried, go back, I don't want you.

10:11.460 --> 10:14.740
Suddenly, a dog ran in front of Alison.

10:16.740 --> 10:20.660
Good dog, good dog, Alison called.

10:22.020 --> 10:25.940
The dog ran to her, and she put her hand on its head.

10:27.540 --> 10:30.900
It was my sister's dog, and it liked her.

10:32.900 --> 10:40.260
It was a big dog, with big teeth, and I didn't like it, because it was always hungry.

10:41.140 --> 10:48.740
I followed Alison, and her dog, along the river to Colne.

10:51.700 --> 10:55.700
But before we arrived at Colne, we met John Law.

10:58.180 --> 11:03.860
John Law was a big fat man, about 50 years old.

11:06.820 --> 11:08.260
Can I have some money, please?

11:09.220 --> 11:11.860
Alison called, I'm hungry.

11:14.980 --> 11:16.980
John Law didn't answer.

11:18.340 --> 11:25.860
He walked slowly, because he was fat, and because he carried a big bag on his back.

11:28.740 --> 11:32.580
In his bag, were a lot of beautiful things.

11:33.540 --> 11:40.020
He was a peddler, and he walked across the hills, and visited all the villages.

11:42.980 --> 11:44.260
Can I have some money?

11:45.140 --> 11:48.580
Alison called again, I'm very hungry.

11:51.220 --> 11:52.580
John Law stopped.

11:53.380 --> 11:54.900
Stop following me.

11:55.780 --> 11:59.780
He said, I'm not going to give you money.

12:00.660 --> 12:03.700
Give me money, Alison said.

12:04.900 --> 12:07.700
I don't want to give you money.

12:08.660 --> 12:12.660
The peddler said, he took his hat off.

12:13.620 --> 12:16.100
There was not much hair on his head.

12:17.540 --> 12:21.940
I don't like you, and I don't like your family.

12:23.140 --> 12:25.860
A lot of bad women you are.

12:26.820 --> 12:30.500
And your father was a bad man, too.

12:32.580 --> 12:33.780
Alison was angry.

12:34.580 --> 12:35.780
Don't talk about my father.

12:36.580 --> 12:37.780
He's dead now.

12:38.980 --> 12:41.220
Give me some money, old man.

12:43.220 --> 12:45.220
John Law's face was red.

12:45.940 --> 12:47.700
No, he cried.

12:50.420 --> 12:53.060
He began to walk up the hill to the village.

12:53.700 --> 12:55.700
Go back to your dirty family.

12:58.340 --> 13:00.340
Alison began to laugh angrily.

13:02.980 --> 13:08.420
A dead man, a dead man, she called.

13:09.380 --> 13:11.380
Dead before dark, John Law.

13:13.140 --> 13:17.780
She looked down at her dog, and put her hand on its head.

13:18.980 --> 13:22.420
She looked down at her dog, and put her hand on its head.

13:23.060 --> 13:25.620
Go after him, dog, she said.

13:26.820 --> 13:30.020
Go after him, and get him.

13:32.900 --> 13:36.420
The big dog began to run after the peddler.

13:37.860 --> 13:39.140
John Law stopped.

13:40.900 --> 13:45.060
He looked afraid, and his face was very red.

13:47.220 --> 13:49.780
Call your dog back, you bad girl.

13:50.740 --> 13:51.540
He shouted.

13:53.300 --> 13:58.820
Suddenly, his mouth opened, and his face went white.

14:01.300 --> 14:08.900
Slowly, he began to fall, and his big body hit the road.

14:11.620 --> 14:16.580
The dog came up to him, but the peddler did not move.

14:16.820 --> 14:22.820
Alison watched John Law for a minute.

14:23.940 --> 14:27.860
Then she said to me, don't call someone from the village.

14:29.860 --> 14:34.260
I felt afraid, but I ran along the road very quickly.

14:35.460 --> 14:36.820
Help! Help!

14:37.380 --> 14:40.500
I called to the villagers. The peddler is ill!

14:43.620 --> 14:45.860
The villagers came out of their houses.

14:46.580 --> 14:48.340
And followed me down the hill.

14:50.020 --> 14:53.300
A young man looked at John Law carefully.

14:54.660 --> 14:58.820
He's not dead, he said, but he's very ill.

15:00.420 --> 15:06.180
Let's move him to the nearest house. Someone must go and call his son.

15:09.220 --> 15:14.420
Just then, John Law began to talk very slowly.

15:15.300 --> 15:20.180
I can't move, you said.

15:21.060 --> 15:26.900
I'm alive, but I can't move.

15:29.140 --> 15:32.500
I went back to stand near Alison.

15:33.700 --> 15:35.940
The dog sat at her feet.

15:37.780 --> 15:41.620
That device, girl.

15:42.020 --> 15:44.660
John Law said slowly.

15:45.940 --> 15:48.980
She, she cursed me.

15:49.460 --> 15:56.740
She wanted me to die and her dog came to get me.

15:58.420 --> 16:01.700
All the villagers looked at Alison.

16:02.660 --> 16:05.300
I'm sorry, Alison said quickly.

16:05.780 --> 16:09.140
I'm very hungry and I wanted some money.

16:09.140 --> 16:11.940
And I wanted some money. That's all.

16:13.460 --> 16:16.180
Go away, the villagers cried.

16:16.980 --> 16:20.260
You're a witch and we don't want you in our village.

16:22.420 --> 16:26.820
Alison began to run away down the hill and her dog followed.

16:28.820 --> 16:30.340
I watched the villagers.

16:31.780 --> 16:36.580
They carried John Law slowly up the hill to the nearest house.

16:36.900 --> 16:41.940
And then I followed my sister down the hill.

16:44.260 --> 16:51.060
I was hungry and tired and milk in tower was many miles away.

16:53.380 --> 16:57.380
I was nine years old and I was angry.

16:59.780 --> 17:02.740
I was angry because the peddler was ill.

17:03.540 --> 17:07.780
I was angry because the villagers didn't like me.

17:09.940 --> 17:14.900
And I was angry because my sister was a witch.

17:18.740 --> 17:21.300
Chapter two, Roger Noel.

17:22.580 --> 17:31.220
John Law was ill because Alison cursed him and his son wanted Roger Noel to question Alison.

17:33.540 --> 17:38.660
Roger Noel was a rich and important man in Lancashire

17:39.620 --> 17:43.060
and he was the judge for all the villagers near Pendle Hill.

17:45.060 --> 17:49.620
He lived at Reed Hall, seven miles from New Church.

17:52.980 --> 17:58.820
On the thirtieth day of March, Mr. Noel's men came to Mulkin Tower.

17:58.980 --> 18:04.580
Mr. Noel wanted to see Alison at once.

18:07.540 --> 18:10.980
We walked from Mulkin Tower to Reed Hall.

18:12.340 --> 18:19.620
My sister Alison, my brother James and our mother Elizabeth Device.

18:22.420 --> 18:27.540
I followed them because I didn't want to stay at home with my grandmother.

18:29.460 --> 18:35.860
My grandmother was a difficult old woman and I didn't like her.

18:38.980 --> 18:45.780
Reed Hall was an old house with a big garden and many old trees.

18:48.420 --> 18:51.700
Mr. Noel's servant opened the door for us.

18:52.420 --> 18:55.620
Come in, Mr. Noel said.

18:56.820 --> 19:01.060
He was a tall man with a lot of white hair.

19:02.820 --> 19:06.820
His black coat looked warm and expensive.

19:09.460 --> 19:13.940
Alison followed Mr. Noel into a room with a big fire.

19:15.860 --> 19:20.340
When I saw the fire, I wanted to go in too.

19:21.220 --> 19:23.460
Are you cold, little one?

19:24.660 --> 19:30.660
Mr. Noel asked me, come in and sit near the fire.

19:33.220 --> 19:40.660
I went across the room and sat down on the floor next to the wonderful hot fire.

19:42.500 --> 19:45.940
Mr. Noel sat behind a big table.

19:46.340 --> 19:52.740
Two or three men in black coats stood near the window.

19:53.620 --> 19:56.820
Alison stood in front of Mr. Noel.

19:57.860 --> 20:05.140
Her long hair was dirty and her old dress looked dirtier.

20:06.740 --> 20:13.380
Two weeks ago, on the 18th day of March,

20:14.180 --> 20:18.580
you met John Lohr near Colne.

20:19.540 --> 20:21.220
Roger Noel said.

20:22.260 --> 20:25.460
His voice was slow and careful.

20:26.740 --> 20:28.740
Tell me about it.

20:30.740 --> 20:34.180
I asked for money, Alison said.

20:36.180 --> 20:42.020
The peddler was very angry and I didn't like him.

20:42.900 --> 20:48.420
I was angry too and I wanted him to die.

20:50.340 --> 20:52.340
Tell me about your dog.

20:54.420 --> 21:01.460
The dog is my friend, Alison said, slowly.

21:02.660 --> 21:08.660
I wanted a friend and I found that dog two months ago.

21:08.740 --> 21:15.380
Two months ago, I told my grandmother and she liked the dog too.

21:17.700 --> 21:20.180
Did the dog run after the peddler?

21:21.780 --> 21:23.060
Yes, of course.

21:24.180 --> 21:28.020
I cursed the peddler and the dog ran after him.

21:29.060 --> 21:34.340
Alison said, I'm sorry now because Mr. Lohr is ill.

21:35.220 --> 21:40.580
She's a witch, one of the men said quietly.

21:43.620 --> 21:48.980
Roger Noel stood up and walked across the room to the door.

21:50.500 --> 21:53.220
James' device, come in.

21:54.180 --> 21:55.940
We want to question you.

21:58.900 --> 22:03.140
James came in and stood next to Alison.

22:05.140 --> 22:13.220
James was 13 years old, nearly a man, but he was afraid of many things.

22:15.140 --> 22:16.340
He began to cry.

22:18.900 --> 22:22.340
Don't be afraid, Mr. Noel said.

22:23.940 --> 22:29.140
We want you to talk about your grandmother, old Demdike.

22:29.140 --> 22:33.300
But Alison wanted to talk.

22:34.180 --> 22:37.060
Don't ask him, she said quickly.

22:39.140 --> 22:43.940
I can tell you about my grandmother because I'm with her every minute of the day.

22:44.980 --> 22:47.780
I go with her from village to village.

22:48.820 --> 22:51.060
I go with her across Pendle Hill.

22:52.100 --> 22:56.660
She asks people for money and food and I help her.

22:56.900 --> 23:04.660
Alison stopped, she looked at James, and then she looked at Mr. Noel.

23:06.820 --> 23:12.260
She cursed a child once and the child died later that year.

23:13.780 --> 23:18.980
And you, James said, you cursed a child too.

23:18.980 --> 23:20.500
Somebody told me.

23:21.940 --> 23:24.820
James suddenly sat down on the floor.

23:25.700 --> 23:28.100
And began to laugh, loudly.

23:29.140 --> 23:30.100
E quiet.

23:31.300 --> 23:33.300
Rodgenol said, boldly.

23:34.980 --> 23:38.180
Alison device, tell me the truth.

23:39.540 --> 23:42.340
Did you curse a child?

23:44.420 --> 23:45.620
Yes, I did.

23:46.420 --> 23:47.380
Alison cried.

23:48.260 --> 23:51.140
The child called me a witch and I was angry.

23:51.140 --> 23:58.340
I cursed the child, but I was sorry when the child died.

24:01.540 --> 24:03.140
James looked up at Alison.

24:04.580 --> 24:05.780
His mouth opened.

24:07.460 --> 24:09.540
The child died, the child died.

24:10.420 --> 24:12.420
He said again and again.

24:15.060 --> 24:19.380
Alison device, you cannot go home again.

24:20.180 --> 24:26.580
Rodgenol said slowly, you must go to the prison and read.

24:28.820 --> 24:30.500
But I need Alison.

24:31.460 --> 24:33.700
My mother shouted angrily from the door.

24:34.980 --> 24:37.780
She takes care of old Bemdike, my mother.

24:41.300 --> 24:46.180
I looked at my mother at her red, angry face.

24:46.260 --> 24:51.220
I looked at Alison in her dirty dress.

24:52.820 --> 24:57.140
And it James on the floor with his mouth open.

25:00.100 --> 25:01.700
And then I looked at Mr. Noel.

25:03.220 --> 25:07.860
His brown eyes were warm and his face was kind.

25:08.740 --> 25:11.380
On the 2nd day of April,

25:11.380 --> 25:19.300
Rodgenol and his men came to Ashlar house near the village of Fence.

25:20.740 --> 25:25.220
Mr. Noel wanted to talk to my grandmother

25:25.220 --> 25:29.620
and we all went with her to Ashlar house.

25:30.980 --> 25:34.820
Fence was not far from Mulkin Tower.

25:34.820 --> 25:39.140
And my grandmother walked there easily.

25:41.940 --> 25:50.740
Old Bemdike was a little old woman with a fat face and no teeth.

25:52.180 --> 25:58.820
She was nearly 80 years old and she was a difficult old woman.

25:58.820 --> 26:10.420
Without Alison, she was more difficult because my mother didn't take care of her.

26:13.780 --> 26:19.060
When I saw Mr. Noel again at Ashlar house, I felt happy.

26:20.740 --> 26:25.700
I looked at his kind face and his warm brown eyes.

26:26.660 --> 26:29.220
And I wanted to be near him.

26:31.860 --> 26:37.060
But there were a lot of people in the room and I was afraid to go to him.

26:40.180 --> 26:44.420
Old Bemdike, I'm going to ask you some questions.

26:45.540 --> 26:46.820
Mr. Noel began.

26:49.860 --> 26:53.060
Old Bemdike was not afraid.

26:53.540 --> 26:59.460
She looked at all the men in their expensive coats and hats.

27:00.740 --> 27:06.340
What can a poor old woman tell you rich men?

27:08.420 --> 27:09.780
She laughed.

27:10.740 --> 27:15.220
And when she laughed, I felt afraid.

27:15.220 --> 27:15.860
Afraid.

27:18.260 --> 27:22.820
My grandmother was going to tell them everything.

27:25.220 --> 27:26.100
And she did.

27:27.460 --> 27:30.980
Twenty years ago, I met the devil.

27:31.940 --> 27:33.300
Old Bemdike said.

27:34.500 --> 27:39.140
He was a boy called Tib and he was my friend.

27:39.780 --> 27:45.060
Then a cat came to visit me, a beautiful cat.

27:46.100 --> 27:50.900
And then a dog, they were all my friends.

27:52.580 --> 27:56.100
Mr. Noel listened quietly to my grandmother.

27:57.460 --> 28:00.980
But some of the men began to talk angrily.

28:02.580 --> 28:05.540
Be careful, you rich men.

28:06.740 --> 28:08.020
My grandmother cried.

28:08.980 --> 28:11.620
I can curse you.

28:13.700 --> 28:16.260
I can kill people.

28:18.420 --> 28:22.740
I make clay pictures of people.

28:24.020 --> 28:28.260
Man, woman or child.

28:30.180 --> 28:32.580
And when I break the clay,

28:33.380 --> 28:39.460
that man, woman or child dies.

28:41.940 --> 28:43.780
People began to shout.

28:44.580 --> 28:45.540
She's a witch.

28:45.940 --> 28:47.140
She must die.

28:48.660 --> 28:49.860
Say no more.

28:50.020 --> 28:52.500
She must die with all her family.

28:54.500 --> 28:56.180
Roger Noel stood up.

28:57.380 --> 28:58.740
Be quiet.

28:59.300 --> 29:02.100
He looked at the guards near the door.

29:03.060 --> 29:06.100
Take her away, he said.

29:07.380 --> 29:10.900
Old Bemdike and her granddaughter, Alizan,

29:10.900 --> 29:15.140
must go to the prison at Lancaster Castle.

29:18.340 --> 29:21.940
The guards took my grandmother by the arms

29:21.940 --> 29:23.940
and carried her out of the door

29:23.940 --> 29:26.500
and put her on a horse.

29:27.060 --> 29:28.900
And put her on a horse.

29:30.980 --> 29:33.700
Everyone ran out of Ashlar house.

29:34.660 --> 29:37.380
They ran after the horses and shouted,

29:38.100 --> 29:39.220
Kill the witch!

29:41.460 --> 29:45.860
I looked for Mr. Noel, but he was on his horse too.

29:47.060 --> 29:50.100
And he followed the guards quickly through the village.

29:52.740 --> 29:55.700
Slowly, I followed my mother

29:56.340 --> 29:57.140
and James.

29:59.460 --> 30:01.380
Mulkin Tower was my home,

30:02.900 --> 30:05.460
but I didn't want to go back there.

30:07.460 --> 30:09.380
I was a little child

30:10.660 --> 30:14.580
and I wanted someone kind to take care of me.

30:18.980 --> 30:21.060
We stayed at home for days

30:22.500 --> 30:24.660
because we were afraid to go out.

30:26.500 --> 30:29.620
James sat in front of the fire

30:30.420 --> 30:33.140
with his dog and talked.

30:35.140 --> 30:38.100
Lancaster Castle, Lancaster Castle,

30:38.740 --> 30:42.500
he said, again and again.

30:44.740 --> 30:48.100
My mother hit me and shouted at me

30:49.060 --> 30:51.300
because she was angry with the rich men.

30:51.300 --> 30:58.580
But after three days, my mother suddenly said,

30:59.940 --> 31:04.820
James, we're hungry and we must eat.

31:07.540 --> 31:09.460
James didn't answer.

31:12.020 --> 31:14.900
My mother went across the room to James

31:15.620 --> 31:16.740
and pulled his hair.

31:17.540 --> 31:19.460
Get up, she shouted.

31:20.260 --> 31:23.860
Go out and find food for us.

31:25.060 --> 31:26.980
Your father isn't here now.

31:27.780 --> 31:29.460
You must find food for us.

31:31.380 --> 31:33.060
She hit him over the head.

31:34.900 --> 31:38.020
James stood up slowly.

31:40.500 --> 31:43.460
Go out and find food, he said.

31:44.340 --> 31:47.300
I must go out and find food.

31:50.180 --> 31:54.580
It was dark and James was out for hours.

31:56.980 --> 32:00.260
But in the morning, he came back with a sheep.

32:02.340 --> 32:05.860
I went to Bali, James said happily.

32:06.740 --> 32:10.180
I got this sheep and now we can eat.

32:12.900 --> 32:13.780
Get up, Janet.

32:14.820 --> 32:17.540
My mother shouted, come and help me.

32:19.620 --> 32:24.260
It was Friday, the 10th day of April.

32:26.020 --> 32:29.540
My family had some friends, poor people,

32:30.660 --> 32:34.020
and on that day, they came to Mulkin Tower.

32:36.260 --> 32:40.500
They came and asked about Old Dendike and Alizan

32:41.700 --> 32:44.420
and they stayed to eat and drink.

32:44.420 --> 32:49.060
I helped my mother.

32:50.740 --> 32:53.460
We cooked the sheep over a big fire

32:54.580 --> 32:56.340
and our visitors ate with us.

32:58.500 --> 33:01.300
At the same time, they drank.

33:03.780 --> 33:07.140
They sat by the fire and drank

33:08.340 --> 33:10.820
and talked about Lancaster Castle.

33:11.700 --> 33:15.940
Let's go there, an old woman cried.

33:16.740 --> 33:23.460
Let's go to Lancaster Castle and find Old Dendike and Alizan.

33:24.740 --> 33:31.380
We can curse the guards and break down the door, my mother said.

33:32.900 --> 33:37.380
Let's bring them home, said an old man.

33:37.460 --> 33:39.940
Janet, bring the bottle.

33:40.500 --> 33:42.900
We need more drink.

33:43.860 --> 33:45.300
Shouted my mother.

33:46.820 --> 33:50.980
I got up and took more drink to my mother.

33:52.340 --> 33:54.340
But I fell over one of the dogs

33:55.380 --> 33:57.780
and the bottle broke on the floor.

33:58.980 --> 34:00.340
The drink was gone.

34:01.780 --> 34:04.340
You bad child!

34:05.300 --> 34:07.220
You bad child!

34:08.180 --> 34:09.220
My mother shouted.

34:10.740 --> 34:12.260
You're a witch too, you know.

34:14.340 --> 34:17.300
She got up and began to hit me.

34:18.580 --> 34:21.940
She hit me over the head and pulled my hair.

34:23.860 --> 34:28.980
An old man laughed and then everyone laughed.

34:28.980 --> 34:34.260
I ran back across the room.

34:36.100 --> 34:37.460
I wasn't a witch.

34:38.820 --> 34:42.820
I was a child nine years old

34:44.100 --> 34:48.100
and I hated my mother and all her friends.

34:51.060 --> 34:54.900
My face felt very hot because I was angry.

34:57.140 --> 34:58.100
I left the room.

34:58.980 --> 35:00.580
And went out of the house.

35:03.620 --> 35:08.260
It was afternoon but the sky was dark with rain.

35:11.060 --> 35:13.060
Pendle Hill was dark too.

35:14.740 --> 35:18.900
It sat quietly and watched me.

35:21.780 --> 35:23.300
I'm going to Mr. Noel.

35:24.260 --> 35:27.140
I said quietly to Pendle Hill.

35:27.140 --> 35:33.940
I'm going to tell him about my mother and her friends.

35:36.900 --> 35:40.020
Chapter 3, A Family of Witches

35:43.780 --> 35:48.740
I ran from Mulkin Tower down the hill into new church.

35:50.500 --> 35:51.780
James followed me.

35:53.460 --> 35:55.380
I want to go to Reed Hall too.

35:56.340 --> 35:57.300
He said.

36:00.020 --> 36:03.780
We ran through the trees to Sabden Brook.

36:05.540 --> 36:09.460
The noise of the river was beautiful in my ears.

36:11.940 --> 36:17.860
We went along the river to the village of Sabden and then it began to rain.

36:20.420 --> 36:24.180
Suddenly we heard the noise of horses behind us.

36:25.380 --> 36:28.500
We got off the road and watched the horses.

36:30.660 --> 36:34.180
It was Roger Noel with some of his men.

36:35.940 --> 36:39.300
They saw us and Mr. Noel stopped.

36:40.980 --> 36:42.580
It's the device children.

36:43.300 --> 36:43.780
He said.

36:45.220 --> 36:46.740
What's your name child?

36:49.140 --> 36:50.260
My name is Janet.

36:50.900 --> 36:53.940
I said we're going to Reed Hall.

36:54.740 --> 36:56.900
I want to talk to you.

36:59.460 --> 37:04.820
Roger Noel looked at me with his warm brown eyes.

37:06.660 --> 37:08.740
Very well, he said.

37:10.180 --> 37:13.140
Come home with me and we can talk.

37:15.860 --> 37:22.980
He lifted me up onto his horse and the horse moved quickly along the road

37:23.700 --> 37:24.900
to the village of Reed.

37:26.340 --> 37:28.420
James ran along behind us.

37:31.140 --> 37:34.900
Very soon we arrived at Reed Hall.

37:36.740 --> 37:42.500
The servant opened the door for us and we went into the warm house.

37:45.620 --> 37:51.300
James came in too and sat down next to me near the fire.

37:53.860 --> 37:58.340
Mr. Noel put his black hat down on the table.

37:59.860 --> 38:03.940
Bring a hot drink and some food for these children.

38:04.820 --> 38:09.220
He told the servant, they're cold and hungry.

38:12.420 --> 38:19.540
The servant brought bread and hot milk for us and James and I ate hungrily.

38:20.420 --> 38:25.620
I felt warm and happy in Mr. Noel's house.

38:26.900 --> 38:29.460
I wanted to stay there all my life.

38:30.740 --> 38:34.100
I never wanted to go back to Mulkin Tower.

38:39.540 --> 38:44.420
When we finished eating, Mr. Noel looked up from his book.

38:45.300 --> 38:47.940
You wanted to talk to me?

38:49.060 --> 38:53.460
He said quietly, well, I'm listening.

38:56.180 --> 39:02.580
I got up, went across the room and stood in front of Mr. Noel.

39:04.820 --> 39:07.700
I'm afraid of my mother.

39:08.980 --> 39:09.620
I began.

39:10.500 --> 39:17.780
I'm afraid because she's a witch and she can kill people.

39:20.180 --> 39:22.500
The room was quiet.

39:24.020 --> 39:29.380
Mr. Noel said nothing, but his brown eyes were kind.

39:32.980 --> 39:38.100
My mother and her friends are at Mulkin Tower.

39:39.060 --> 39:46.260
I told him, they want to go to Lancaster Castle and kill the guards.

39:47.940 --> 39:51.940
They're going to bring old Demdike and Alison home again.

39:55.220 --> 39:58.100
Mr. Noel got up and left the room.

39:59.860 --> 40:04.660
After some time, he came back with two of his friends.

40:04.900 --> 40:07.700
They all sat down at the table.

40:08.980 --> 40:15.540
Janet, I want you to tell me again about your mother and her friends.

40:17.540 --> 40:21.380
They want to kill the guards at Lancaster Castle

40:21.380 --> 40:24.660
and bring old Demdike home to Mulkin Tower.

40:26.660 --> 40:30.500
I said, then I began to cry.

40:30.500 --> 40:31.700
I began to cry.

40:33.460 --> 40:40.020
Don't cry, Mr. Noel said, kindly, we can help you.

40:41.140 --> 40:43.220
But we must talk to your brother first.

40:44.740 --> 40:50.100
James, he called, tell me about your mother.

40:51.700 --> 40:52.660
Is she a witch?

40:55.140 --> 40:58.340
She's a witch. We're all witches.

40:59.300 --> 41:00.260
James began.

41:01.060 --> 41:02.580
Old Demdike's a witch.

41:04.020 --> 41:07.380
One night, she went to the church at New Church

41:07.380 --> 41:09.860
and got some teeth from dead bodies there.

41:11.540 --> 41:15.860
The devil talked to her and she brought the teeth to Mulkin Tower.

41:16.820 --> 41:19.380
They're under the ground by our door.

41:22.260 --> 41:25.300
Old Demdike's witch, we know that.

41:26.180 --> 41:30.660
Mr. Noel said, tell us about your mother.

41:33.140 --> 41:36.100
Mother's a witch, James said.

41:37.140 --> 41:40.100
She killed Mr. Robinson from Barley Village.

41:40.820 --> 41:44.580
She made a clay picture and then she broke it.

41:45.220 --> 41:48.900
And Mr. Robinson died a week later.

41:51.380 --> 41:53.780
James smiled at Mr. Noel.

41:55.540 --> 41:59.860
He liked Mr. Noel because Mr. Noel didn't shout at him.

42:01.860 --> 42:05.700
And I'm a witch too. I can kill people.

42:06.980 --> 42:12.980
No, James, I cried. You're not a witch. You don't kill people.

42:14.580 --> 42:15.780
Yes, I do.

42:16.980 --> 42:21.140
James said angrily. His face went red.

42:21.300 --> 42:26.820
My dog, Dandy, is the devil.

42:27.620 --> 42:29.860
And he killed a man for me.

42:31.460 --> 42:38.020
I wanted a shirt and Mr. Duckworth was going to give me one of his old shirts.

42:38.020 --> 42:40.980
But in the end, he didn't give it to me.

42:41.540 --> 42:43.780
And I was very angry.

42:45.220 --> 42:48.100
I nearly killed Mr. Duckworth.

42:48.980 --> 42:54.420
But I called Dandy and he killed Mr. Duckworth for me.

42:57.620 --> 42:59.220
I began to cry.

43:00.820 --> 43:03.700
My brother was a witch too.

43:05.460 --> 43:08.660
All my family were witches.

43:10.740 --> 43:12.340
Don't cry, Janet.

43:13.300 --> 43:14.500
Mr. Noel said,

43:15.380 --> 43:17.780
someone must take care of you.

43:19.140 --> 43:23.540
You can stay here at Reed Hall with me.

43:26.260 --> 43:30.020
When Mr. Noel's men brought my mother to Reed Hall,

43:31.540 --> 43:34.260
she said nothing at first.

43:36.260 --> 43:38.500
Tell us about the pictures of Clay.

43:40.180 --> 43:41.300
Mr. Noel said,

43:41.700 --> 43:48.180
my men found pictures of Clay at Mulkin Tower.

43:51.140 --> 43:53.140
My mother said nothing.

43:55.540 --> 44:00.100
Your mother, old Dandyke, is a witch.

44:01.540 --> 44:03.860
Your daughter is a witch.

44:05.460 --> 44:06.500
Mr. Noel said,

44:06.580 --> 44:12.820
your son killed Mr. Duckworth because of a shirt.

44:14.580 --> 44:18.820
Now tell us about the Clay pictures.

44:21.780 --> 44:24.260
My mother said nothing.

44:26.340 --> 44:29.940
James told us about Mr. Robinson of Bali.

44:31.140 --> 44:32.180
Mr. Noel said,

44:34.180 --> 44:35.220
did you kill him?

44:37.380 --> 44:44.020
Suddenly, my mother's face went red and she began to shout at James.

44:45.140 --> 44:46.500
A good son, you are.

44:47.060 --> 44:50.660
You told this rich man about Jack Robinson of Bali.

44:51.460 --> 44:54.100
Well, you told the truth.

44:55.060 --> 44:56.740
I killed him.

44:57.620 --> 45:01.620
I made a Clay picture and then I broke it.

45:02.740 --> 45:05.780
And a week later, he died.

45:07.140 --> 45:10.980
I killed him because I hated him.

45:14.020 --> 45:16.500
She stopped and looked at me.

45:18.260 --> 45:19.860
I wanted to run away,

45:20.740 --> 45:23.860
but Mr. Noel's servant stood in front of the door.

45:26.020 --> 45:28.500
Then my mother laughed.

45:29.380 --> 45:31.380
Heh heh heh heh.

45:31.380 --> 45:36.580
Genet device, witches daughter, you hate us.

45:37.140 --> 45:38.340
I know that.

45:39.380 --> 45:43.780
Well, it doesn't matter because you're right.

45:44.580 --> 45:46.100
You are different.

45:47.460 --> 45:52.580
You're my daughter, but you're not the daughter of my husband.

45:53.460 --> 45:59.780
Your father was a rich man, but he never gave me money.

46:01.060 --> 46:03.780
A witch's child, he called you.

46:05.220 --> 46:10.260
And when you were born, he never came near me again.

46:12.020 --> 46:15.540
Jack Robinson lent the truth about your father.

46:16.180 --> 46:22.900
He told the villagers of Bali and they called me a bad woman.

46:24.020 --> 46:26.820
But they didn't call your father a bad man.

46:28.740 --> 46:34.500
Nobody in Bali gave me food again because of Jack Robinson.

46:36.500 --> 46:41.620
I hated him and so I killed him.

46:41.620 --> 46:50.580
The room was very quiet and my mother laughed again.

46:54.980 --> 47:02.580
My hands felt cold and my face was hot but I didn't cry.

47:05.300 --> 47:09.780
When Mr. Device died, I cried for days.

47:11.700 --> 47:13.620
But he was not my father.

47:16.340 --> 47:25.940
I looked at my mother at her dirty hair and her ugly face at her angry eyes.

47:28.260 --> 47:34.340
I hated her then and I hated her for many years.

47:34.900 --> 47:39.460
Chapter 4, truth and lies.

47:39.460 --> 47:49.220
On the 27th day of April, the guards took my mother and James to Lancaster Castle.

47:49.220 --> 47:54.020
And my life at Reed Hall began.

47:54.020 --> 47:56.900
Suddenly it was spring.

47:56.900 --> 48:01.700
The sky was blue and there were beautiful things.

48:01.780 --> 48:05.460
Blue and there were beautiful flowers on the hills.

48:07.300 --> 48:11.060
From Reed Hall, Pendle Hill looked different.

48:12.180 --> 48:16.660
It looked smaller and it was not so important in my life.

48:19.540 --> 48:26.340
Sometimes I walked along Sabden Brook to Sabden and then to New Church

48:27.380 --> 48:30.820
and I felt happy to be near Pendle Hill again.

48:32.500 --> 48:35.860
But I never visited Mulkin Tower again.

48:38.820 --> 48:45.780
Spring changed into summer and in August I went to Lancaster with Mr. Noel.

48:47.460 --> 48:56.180
Lancaster was 30 miles from Reed Hall and I got very tired because I sat on a horse for hours.

48:56.820 --> 49:01.220
It was a big noisy town.

49:02.180 --> 49:08.740
I never saw so many people before in my life and I felt afraid.

49:11.460 --> 49:19.060
The trial of the witches of Pendle began at Lancaster Castle on the 18th day of August

49:20.260 --> 49:23.380
and the judge was an important man from London.

49:24.180 --> 49:33.380
Judge Bromley listened to many people on that day because there were a lot of witches from Lancashire in the prison.

49:35.380 --> 49:43.380
Old Dendike was not there because she died in May before the judge arrived.

49:45.380 --> 49:52.260
I waited with Mr. Noel's servant and when a guard called my name,

49:52.660 --> 49:58.660
I went through a big door and saw the judge behind a table.

50:00.820 --> 50:07.940
Judge Bromley was rich and important but his eyes were cold.

50:10.340 --> 50:13.380
Suddenly I saw my mother.

50:15.060 --> 50:18.020
She was dirty and very thin.

50:18.820 --> 50:23.620
When she saw me, her face went red.

50:25.700 --> 50:32.020
My hair was clean now and I wore shoes and an expensive dress.

50:33.620 --> 50:35.620
I saw my mother's eyes.

50:37.220 --> 50:38.820
She hated me.

50:41.220 --> 50:43.220
Are you a witch?

50:44.420 --> 50:46.420
Judge Bromley asked my mother.

50:48.500 --> 50:49.460
No, I'm not.

50:50.660 --> 50:52.580
My mother answered angrily.

50:54.420 --> 50:58.820
Did you kill Jack Robinson of Barley Village?

51:00.980 --> 51:02.180
No, I did not.

51:04.100 --> 51:05.780
Janet's device is here.

51:06.980 --> 51:08.580
A voice said quietly.

51:10.180 --> 51:11.380
It was Mr. Noel.

51:13.140 --> 51:15.620
She can tell us the truth about her mother.

51:18.980 --> 51:22.340
For a minute, my mother did not move.

51:24.740 --> 51:28.260
And she ran across the room and shouted at me.

51:30.500 --> 51:33.940
You know nothing, you bad child.

51:34.900 --> 51:36.660
And I'm your mother.

51:37.460 --> 51:38.660
Don't forget that.

51:40.740 --> 51:44.820
The guards ran after my mother and pulled her to the floor.

51:45.620 --> 51:48.100
I'm now witch.

51:49.300 --> 51:52.500
My mother shouted, it's all lies.

51:53.860 --> 51:57.940
Janet, you're a witch, a child of the devil.

51:59.220 --> 52:02.980
You're my daughter and I know.

52:06.580 --> 52:10.820
I was afraid and I put my hands over my eyes.

52:11.620 --> 52:15.860
I didn't want to see my mother's ugly face.

52:17.700 --> 52:23.140
The guards pulled my mother out of the room and the noise stopped.

52:24.900 --> 52:28.180
Janet's device, the judge said,

52:28.980 --> 52:32.180
tell us the truth about your mother.

52:32.180 --> 52:41.380
Roger Noel lifted me up and put me on a table in front of the judge.

52:44.100 --> 52:46.020
My mother is a witch.

52:47.220 --> 52:47.860
I began.

52:49.540 --> 52:53.300
She has a friend, a dog called Ball.

52:55.060 --> 52:58.660
When she wants to kill somebody, she tells Ball.

52:59.540 --> 53:03.380
I talked and talked.

53:04.740 --> 53:06.980
I told the judge everything.

53:10.420 --> 53:12.740
Judge Bromley listened carefully.

53:14.500 --> 53:17.140
My child, is this the truth?

53:19.300 --> 53:21.060
Yes, I answered.

53:22.420 --> 53:23.780
I'm telling you the truth.

53:24.580 --> 53:30.980
The guards brought my mother back into the room again.

53:32.580 --> 53:36.580
Her face looked tired and her eyes were red.

53:38.580 --> 53:44.820
Elizabeth, device, your daughter told us about your dog, Ball.

53:46.500 --> 53:50.420
Your son, too, told us about the clay pictures.

53:50.500 --> 53:53.940
We know everything.

53:56.900 --> 53:58.740
My mother said nothing.

53:59.700 --> 54:04.820
She didn't look at the judge and she didn't look at me.

54:07.540 --> 54:12.420
Next, the guards brought my brother James into the room.

54:13.860 --> 54:17.460
When I saw James, I wanted to cry.

54:18.100 --> 54:24.740
James was thin and dirty, and his hair was very long.

54:27.380 --> 54:32.660
He looked at the judge and had all the rich and important men in the room.

54:34.260 --> 54:35.860
And he began to cry.

54:37.540 --> 54:39.620
Then he sat down on the floor.

54:40.660 --> 54:42.420
Stand up, James, device.

54:43.700 --> 54:45.060
Judge Bromley said.

54:45.620 --> 54:46.820
Judge Bromley said.

54:48.980 --> 54:53.460
The guards pulled James up, but he fell to the floor again.

54:55.060 --> 54:59.540
You killed Mr Duckworth, Judge Bromley said.

55:01.220 --> 55:02.900
I wanted a shirt.

55:04.500 --> 55:05.460
James cried.

55:07.700 --> 55:09.300
Is your brother a witch?

55:10.580 --> 55:12.020
Judge Bromley asked me.

55:12.820 --> 55:14.660
Yes, I said.

55:16.100 --> 55:18.660
My brother sat on the floor.

55:19.140 --> 55:21.140
His mouth opened.

55:22.580 --> 55:26.980
He looked at me, but he didn't know me.

55:28.820 --> 55:33.460
I was clean and fat because of all the good food at Reed Hall.

55:35.060 --> 55:38.900
James told me about his friend, Dandy.

55:39.700 --> 55:40.900
I began.

55:42.740 --> 55:49.380
Dandy was the devil and James heard the name Dandy, and he began to cry again.

55:50.980 --> 55:54.500
I want Dandy. I want to go home.

55:57.300 --> 56:01.620
The guards pulled him up from the floor and took him out of the room.

56:03.140 --> 56:04.900
I never saw my brother again.

56:05.060 --> 56:15.780
When the guards brought my sister Alison in front of the judge, I said nothing.

56:17.780 --> 56:21.780
John Law, the peddler, came into the room.

56:23.620 --> 56:25.140
He was a thin man now.

56:26.500 --> 56:33.700
He walked slowly, and he talked slowly, and his face looked ill.

56:35.780 --> 56:43.380
He told the judge about that day near cold when Alison cursed him, and her dog ran after him.

56:45.060 --> 56:51.460
I'm sorry, Alison said. I was angry with you that day, but I'm sorry now.

56:53.700 --> 57:00.980
Alison's eyes were dark and afraid, but she had no friends in that room.

57:01.780 --> 57:04.420
And nobody wanted to listen to her.

57:07.380 --> 57:13.380
Then Mr. Knoll took me out, and I waited with his servant in a different room.

57:16.020 --> 57:21.540
An hour later, there was the noise of many people shouting and crying.

57:23.220 --> 57:24.500
The servant smiled.

57:25.380 --> 57:32.020
The trial is finished. He said, you're a good child, Janet.

57:32.020 --> 57:35.220
You told the judge the truth about the witches.

57:38.340 --> 57:41.540
Mr. Knoll took me home to read hall.

57:42.900 --> 57:49.620
And on the 20th day of August, 1612, the guards took my mother,

57:50.260 --> 58:00.580
my sister, and my brother out of prison and hanged them in front of Lancaster Castle.

58:04.340 --> 58:08.100
And so I lost my family.

58:11.860 --> 58:16.020
When I was a child, I wanted to be happy.

58:16.340 --> 58:23.700
I wanted to be warm, to wear shoes, to eat good food.

58:23.700 --> 58:28.100
I wanted someone to take care of me.

58:29.380 --> 58:30.020
That's all.

58:31.700 --> 58:33.220
My mother gave me nothing.

58:34.660 --> 58:38.980
She gave me no love. She never took care of me.

58:40.820 --> 58:45.220
Because my mother was a witch, my father ran away.

58:46.260 --> 58:48.260
And I never knew him.

58:50.820 --> 58:53.540
My father was a rich man without a name.

58:54.820 --> 59:00.420
And I lived hungry and cold with a witch.

59:02.660 --> 59:06.820
And so I told Judge Bromley the truth about my family.

59:09.220 --> 59:09.940
Was I wrong?

59:12.020 --> 59:12.660
I don't know.

59:16.260 --> 59:18.900
I was happy for years at read hall.

59:19.780 --> 59:23.460
For 21 years, I forgot my family.

59:24.900 --> 59:27.140
I learned to cook for the Knoll family.

59:28.260 --> 59:30.500
I worked many hours every day.

59:31.380 --> 59:34.340
But I was warm, and I ate good food.

59:36.340 --> 59:40.900
Every Sunday, in my best dress, I went to church.

59:41.780 --> 59:46.340
Every summer, I walked over Pendle Hill.

59:47.540 --> 59:53.700
I never thought about my family, because I was happy, at read hall.

59:56.500 --> 01:00:04.340
In August, 1612, the guards hanged my family in front of Lancaster Castle.

01:00:06.100 --> 01:00:10.500
But their dead faces, waited for me there.

01:00:11.780 --> 01:00:21.540
And a year ago, in 1633, when the guards put me in the prison in Lancaster Castle,

01:00:22.900 --> 01:00:24.900
I met them again.

01:00:26.820 --> 01:00:36.900
Day after day, I see their ugly, dead faces, and hear their cold, angry voices.

01:00:37.460 --> 01:00:41.620
I think of them, all the time.

01:00:43.140 --> 01:00:45.940
God is with me here, in prison.

01:00:46.820 --> 01:00:48.100
I believe that.

01:00:49.300 --> 01:00:52.500
But my dead family is with me too.

01:00:55.700 --> 01:01:01.140
Mr. Webster, from the church at Kildwick, visits me again.

01:01:02.500 --> 01:01:04.500
His blue eyes are tired.

01:01:05.140 --> 01:01:07.140
But he smiles at me.

01:01:09.620 --> 01:01:14.420
Edmund Rogginson and his father told the truth in London.

01:01:15.620 --> 01:01:23.220
He says quietly, the child told lies about you, because he was afraid of his father.

01:01:24.900 --> 01:01:26.900
He wanted his father to love him.

01:01:29.700 --> 01:01:31.700
I say nothing.

01:01:32.580 --> 01:01:38.020
Mr. Webster wants to be kind, but he cannot help me.

01:01:38.820 --> 01:01:42.820
Mr. Noel cannot help me, because he is dead.

01:01:45.060 --> 01:01:48.500
Edmund Rogginson is only a child.

01:01:49.460 --> 01:01:54.100
He tells lies one day, and the truth the next day.

01:01:55.460 --> 01:01:57.460
But the truth cannot help me.

01:01:58.020 --> 01:01:59.860
But the truth cannot help me.

01:02:02.100 --> 01:02:05.780
What can I do against hate and lies?

01:02:09.140 --> 01:02:13.780
When Mr. Noel was alive, the villagers didn't talk about me.

01:02:15.460 --> 01:02:19.380
But when Mr. Noel died, the lies began.

01:02:21.620 --> 01:02:26.900
The villagers are all afraid of me, because my name is device.

01:02:28.420 --> 01:02:32.580
They hate me, because my name is device.

01:02:34.980 --> 01:02:40.500
They say, I am a witch, because my name is device.

01:02:43.460 --> 01:02:48.820
I come from a family of witches, but I am not a witch.

01:02:50.980 --> 01:02:53.380
Nobody died because I cursed them.

01:02:54.260 --> 01:03:01.060
I never made clay pictures, I never had a cat or dog.

01:03:03.060 --> 01:03:11.860
I only wanted to live quietly at Reed Hall, and watch the changing skies over Pendle Hill.

01:03:15.700 --> 01:03:20.500
When I was a child, I was always cold and hungry,

01:03:21.460 --> 01:03:25.060
and I hated my family, because they were witches.

01:03:26.900 --> 01:03:33.780
In 1612, I told the truth, and the truth killed my family.

01:03:36.100 --> 01:03:46.340
Now, 22 years later, lies are going to kill me, here in Lancaster Castle,

01:03:46.340 --> 01:03:52.180
and I am cold and hungry again.

01:03:55.540 --> 01:04:00.100
Mr. Webster gives me bread, and I go back into the prison.

01:04:01.860 --> 01:04:06.260
I can never go back to Reed Hall. I know that now.

01:04:08.100 --> 01:04:13.780
I must stay here in Lancaster Castle, with my dead family.

01:04:14.420 --> 01:04:19.620
They are watching me, and waiting for me.

01:04:21.380 --> 01:04:22.980
I can never be free of them.

01:04:25.300 --> 01:04:38.500
This is my true story, and I want to finish it, now.

